alert.note: Alert for Central Coast; Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca; North Coast; Western Strait of Juan De Fuca (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 23 at 3:52PM PST until December 24 at 3:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 3 PM PST SATURDAY... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected. * WHERE...Eastern Strait of Juan de Fuca, Western Strait of Juan De Fuca, North Coast and Central Coast zones. * WHEN...From 10 AM to 3 PM PST Saturday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of lots, parks, and roads with only isolated road closures expected. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...King tides will result in unusually high water levels at high tide. Minor tidal overflow and coastal erosion is possible. Similar conditions are expected Sunday.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
